              "id": "s1",
              "text_en": "The simplest free body diagram. A book resting on a table."
            },
            {
              "id": "s2",
              "text_en": "Isolate the book. Remove the table, and the contact becomes an upward normal reaction. Gravity still pulls straight down."
            },
            {
              "id": "s3",
              "text_en": "Two forces: N upward and mg downward. Sum of forces in y equals N minus mg equals zero, so N equals mg equals four point nine newtons."
            },
            {
              "id": "s4",
              "text_en": "This template repeats for every problem. Isolate the body, replace each contact with an arrow, apply Newton's law."
            }
